pdqninja.pdqio
Class FileStoreIterator

java.lang.Object
  pdqninja.util.WeightedLoopIterator<File>
      pdqninja.pdqio.FileStoreIterator
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterator<File>
public class FileStoreIterator
extends WeightedLoopIterator<File>

Iterates over directories in a File Store.

A File Store is a set of directories that constitute one logical storage division. As an example, on a computer with two hard drives that are mounted at / and /mnt/disk2, one may assign a temporary storage area consisting of these two directories: /tmp and /mnt/disk2/tmp. In this way, the I/O operations for temporary files can be spread out across the two hard drives. Optionally, the different directories in a File Store can be assigned relative weights, in which case, the I/O operations are divided across the directories in that ratio.

A FileStoreIterator is a WeightedLoopIterator that iterates in a loop over the different directories that constitute a File Store.

A new file can be created in the "current" directory (that is, the directory last return by the WeightedLoopIterator.next()) via the createFile(String) method.

This iterator can also be provided with a collection of files. The getFiles() method returns a subset of these files which belong to the current directory.

getFiles

public Collection<File> getFiles()
Returns a view of all the files in the current directory, or null if no files exist. The returned value is a view, so any change to the collection will be reflected in the subsequent calls.

Returns:
View of all the file in this directory, or null if there are no files.
Throws:
IOException
IllegalStateException - if this method is called before calling WeightedLoopIterator.next() or after calling WeightedLoopIterator.remove()
